translation.en: So, we meet in a train station.
translation.es: Nos encontramos en una estación de tren.

translation.en: You know anything about birds, Jack?
Birds of a feather flock together.
translation.es: Las aves de igual plumaje hacen el mismo viaje.
Un concepto que se cree fundamental.

translation.en: For a while, I lived near a farm.
translation.es: Por un tiempo viví cerca de una granja.

translation.en: If my train was on time, I wouldn't even be here now.
translation.es: Si mi tren no estuviera retrasado, ni siquiera estaría aquí.

translation.en: You are a strong- arm man?
Well, there is no Santa Claus.
I won't be here for Christmas.
But the ladies have been talking, Jack.
translation.es: Pero las chicas han estado hablando, Jack.

translation.en: Right. With the Easter Bunny, I suppose.
translation.es: Claro, imagino que con el conejo de Pascua.

translation.en: Is that what you want me to believe?
translation.es: ¿Eso es lo que quieres que crea?

translation.en: You'll not get a free lunch around here.
translation.es: No me des gato por liebre.

translation.en: Don't you ever wonder about anything?
The wonder was in my heart,
but you wouldn't understand something like that.
translation.es: pero tú no entenderías algo así.

translation.en: There's an elephant in the room.
translation.es: Hay un asunto que estamos evitando.

translation.en: I'd like you to start talking turkey.
translation.es: Quiero que empieces a soltar la lengua.

translation.en: I ordered coffee about a half hour ago.
All the outgoing trains are stopped.
The place is crawling with hungry passengers and cops.
translation.es: Este lugar está lleno de pasajeros hambrientos y policías.

translation.en: It seems there's a murderer on the loose.
translation.es: Parece que hay un asesino suelto.

translation.en: Are you now or have you ever been
a card- carrying member of the Communist Party?
Let me tell you a story.
My father was a pipefitter for the DeWitt family.
translation.es: Mi padre era el fontanero de la familia DeWitt.

translation.en: I would've laid my life on the line for any chicken
translation.es: Habría arriesgado mi vida por cualquier gallina
Soy especialista en bolsas de plástico.

translation.en: You'd toss an animal up on a roof just to see the look on its face.
translation.es: Arrojarías un animal al techo solo para ver la expresión que pone.

translation.en: I'm lucky to have my life,
let alone the hair on my body.
translation.es: Ni hablemos de conservar mi pelaje.

translation.en: Are you going to drink your coffee?
Maybe I will, maybe I won't.
translation.es: Puede que sí, puede que no.

translation.en: Are you calling me a liar?
I know why the chicken crossed the road.
translation.es: Sé por qué la gallina cruzó la calle.

translation.en: This conversation just came to a screeching halt.
Be a man, Jack, and tell me about her.
translation.es: Sé un hombre, Jack, y cuéntame sobre ella.

translation.en: You think you just rolled a seven?
translation.es: ¿Crees que tienes un as bajo la manga?

translation.en: I used to hang out with clowns like you.
translation.es: Yo solía salir con payasos como tú.

translation.en: Never mention that place to me again.
translation.es: Nunca vuelvas a mencionarme ese lugar.

translation.en: Don't you have any sense of decency?
translation.es: ¿No tienes ni un poco de decencia?

translation.en: No one was with her that night.
translation.es: No había nadie con ella esa noche.

translation.en: She was all alone, waiting for you.
You were so sure she was with someone that you never showed.
translation.es: Estabas tan seguro de que estaba con alguien que no fuiste.

translation.en: Don't you know that she cried all night long over you?
translation.es: ¿No sabes que lloró toda la noche por ti?

translation.en: Right or wrong, she loved you.
translation.es: Para bien o para mal, ella te amaba.

translation.en: This thing is bigger than both of us.
translation.es: Esto va más allá de ti y de mí.

translation.en: I'm telling you how it was for real.
translation.es: Te estoy diciendo lo que realmente pasó.

translation.en: You have no proof Max left the club.
translation.es: No tienes pruebas de que Max se fuera del club.

translation.en: No matter. I saw it all in her eyes.
translation.es: No importa. Lo vi todo en sus ojos.

translation.en: I saw her from the window when she leaned out to see him get his tab.
translation.es: La vi por la ventana cuando se inclinó a verlo pagar la cuenta.

translation.en: And that's when you shot him.

translation.es: ¿Quién va a creerle a un orangután?

translation.en: I'll see you and raise you five.
translation.es: Acepto tu apuesta y subo cinco.
El tango se baila de a dos, Jack.
La fiesta se había terminado, vaquero.
Todos se habían ido a sus casa.

translation.en: and the janitor is standing by with his whore named Sally.
translation.es: y el conserje estaba listo con su prostituta llamada Sally.

translation.en: Shelby was banging Sally like there was no tomorrow
translation.es: Shelby se cogía a Sally como si el mundo fuera a terminarse

translation.en: And he had his eye on Toototabon.

translation.en: I have a Buck knife which I only use going into the wild.
translation.es: Solo tengo una navaja que uso cuando voy a cazar.

translation.en: I once sliced a gator that was going after a rabbit friend.
translation.es: Una vez rebané a un caimán que perseguía a un conejo amigo mío.

translation.en: I'd only seen a red rabbit in a dream.
translation.es: solo había visto un conejo rojo en un sueño.

translation.en: Suffers from advanced stages of gonorrhea.
He could have shot Max that night.
translation.es: Él podría haberle disparado a Max esa noche.

translation.en: Okay, let's go back to the beginning.
Life in those times was hard.
translation.es: La vida en esa época era dura.

translation.en: Hard enough to crack a coconut.
translation.es: Tan dura que podía partir un coco.

translation.en: let's say I was a horse.
translation.es: digamos que yo fuera un caballo.

translation.en: Even so, it'd be hard to imagine
how hard my first wife rode my ass.
translation.es: cuánto me fustigaba mi primera esposa.

translation.en: and not necessarily of what you could call good health.
translation.es: y no gozo particularmente de buena salud.

translation.en: But I took it from her for six long years.
translation.es: Pero la soporté durante seis largos años.

translation.en: Finally some banshee killed her out in the bush.
translation.es: Finalmente, un alma en pena la mató en el bosque.

translation.en: I thought I'd died and gone to heaven.
translation.es: Creí morir e ir al cielo.

translation.en: The freedom I felt was extraordinary.
translation.es: La libertad que sentí fue extraordinaria.

translation.en: she really was my first love.
They say real love is a banana,
translation.es: Dicen que el amor verdadero es como un plátano:

translation.en: I'd never been with a chicken before.
translation.es: Nunca había estado con una gallina.

translation.en: In my mind's eye, I can still see her.
translation.es: Aún la veo en mi mente.

translation.en: It's all like a crazy nightmare to me now.
translation.es: Ahora todo parece una pesadilla atroz.

translation.en: you get your hands up under those feathers
translation.es: Cuando metes las manos por debajo de esas plumas

translation.en: There's nothing like it in this world.
translation.es: No hay nada en el mundo que se le parezca.

translation.en: She was the love of my life.
translation.es: Ella fue el amor de mi vida.

translation.en: She and I lit the flame of love.

De la llama del amor verdadero

translation.en: Hands up against the wall, Jack.
translation.es: Las manos contra la pared, Jack.

translation.en: You're under arrest for the murder of Max Clegg.
translation.es: Quedas arrestado por el asesinato de Max Clegg.

translation.en: Cuff him, boys, and take him in.
